01020 /**
01021  * cvmx_npi_base_addr_input#
01022  *
01023  * NPI_BASE_ADDR_INPUT0 = NPI's Base Address Input 0 Register
01024  *
01025  * The address to start reading Instructions from for Input-0.
01026  */
01027 union cvmx_npi_base_addr_inputx {
01028     uint64_t u64;
01029     struct cvmx_npi_base_addr_inputx_s {
01030 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
01031     uint64_t baddr                        : 61; /**< The address to read Instruction from for output 0.
01032                                                          This address is 8-byte aligned, for this reason
01033                                                          address bits [2:0] will always be zero. */
01034     uint64_t reserved_0_2                 : 3;
01035 #else
01036     uint64_t reserved_0_2                 : 3;
01037     uint64_t baddr                        : 61;
01038 #endif
01039     } s;
01040     struct cvmx_npi_base_addr_inputx_s    cn30xx;
01041     struct cvmx_npi_base_addr_inputx_s    cn31xx;
01042     struct cvmx_npi_base_addr_inputx_s    cn38xx;
01043     struct cvmx_npi_base_addr_inputx_s    cn38xxp2;
01044     struct cvmx_npi_base_addr_inputx_s    cn50xx;
01045     struct cvmx_npi_base_addr_inputx_s    cn58xx;
01046     struct cvmx_npi_base_addr_inputx_s    cn58xxp1;
01047 };
01048 typedef union cvmx_npi_base_addr_inputx cvmx_npi_base_addr_inputx_t;

01050 /**

01291 /**
01292  * cvmx_npi_ctl_status
01293  *
01294  * NPI_CTL_STATUS = NPI's Control Status Register
01295  *
01296  * Contains control ans status for NPI.
01297  * Writes to this register are not ordered with writes/reads to the PCI Memory space.
01298  * To ensure that a write has completed the user must read the register before
01299  * making an access(i.e. PCI memory space) that requires the value of this register to be updated.
01300  */

01308                                                          Registers are disabled. */
01309     uint64_t out3_enb                     : 1;  /**< When asserted '1' the output3 engine is enabled.
01310                                                          After enabling the values of the associated
01311                                                          Address and Size Register should not be changed. */

01313                                                          After enabling the values of the associated
01314                                                          Address and Size Register should not be changed. */

01316                                                          After enabling the values of the associated
01317                                                          Address and Size Register should not be changed. */
01318     uint64_t out0_enb                     : 1;  /**< When asserted '1' the output0 engine is enabled.
01319                                                          After enabling the values of the associated
01320                                                          Address and Size Register should not be changed. */
01321     uint64_t ins3_enb                     : 1;  /**< When asserted '1' the gather3 engine is enabled.
01322                                                          After enabling the values of the associated
01323                                                          Address and Size Register should not be changed. */
01324     uint64_t ins2_enb                     : 1;  /**< When asserted '1' the gather2 engine is enabled.
01325                                                          After enabling the values of the associated
01326                                                          Address and Size Register should not be changed. */
01327     uint64_t ins1_enb                     : 1;  /**< When asserted '1' the gather1 engine is enabled.
01328                                                          After enabling the values of the associated
01329                                                          Address and Size Register should not be changed. */
01330     uint64_t ins0_enb                     : 1;  /**< When asserted '1' the gather0 engine is enabled.
01331                                                          After enabling the values of the associated
01332                                                          Address and Size Register should not be changed. */

01334                                                          gather3 engine are 64-Byte instructions, when

01346                                                          PNI address range 0x1000 - 0x17FF from the PCI. */

01348                                                          from the L2C before sending additional access to

01464                                                          PNI address range 0x1000 - 0x17FF from the PCI. */
01465     uint64_t wait_com                     : 1;  /**< When set '1' casues the NPI to wait for a commit
01466                                                          from the L2C before sending additional access to
01467                                                          the L2C from the PCI. */
01468     uint64_t reserved_37_39               : 3;
01469     uint64_t max_word                     : 5;  /**< The maximum number of words to merge into a single
01470                                                          write operation from the PPs to the PCI. Legal
01471                                                          values are 1 to 32, where a '0' is treated as 32. */
01472     uint64_t reserved_10_31               : 22;
01473     uint64_t timer                        : 10; /**< When the NPI starts a PP to PCI write it will wait
01474                                                          no longer than the value of TIMER in eclks to
01475                                                          merge additional writes from the PPs into 1
01476                                                          large write. The values for this field is 1 to
01477                                                          1024 where a value of '0' is treated as 1024. */
01478 #else
01479     uint64_t timer                        : 10;
01480     uint64_t reserved_10_31               : 22;
01481     uint64_t max_word                     : 5;
01482     uint64_t reserved_37_39               : 3;
01483     uint64_t wait_com                     : 1;
01484     uint64_t pci_wdis                     : 1;
01485     uint64_t ins0_64b                     : 1;
01486     uint64_t ins1_64b                     : 1;
01487     uint64_t reserved_44_45               : 2;
01488     uint64_t ins0_enb                     : 1;
01489     uint64_t ins1_enb                     : 1;
01490     uint64_t reserved_48_49               : 2;
01491     uint64_t out0_enb                     : 1;
01492     uint64_t out1_enb                     : 1;
01493     uint64_t reserved_52_53               : 2;
01494     uint64_t dis_pniw                     : 1;
01495     uint64_t chip_rev                     : 8;
01496     uint64_t reserved_63_63               : 1;
01497 #endif
01498     } cn31xx;
01499     struct cvmx_npi_ctl_status_s          cn38xx;
01500     struct cvmx_npi_ctl_status_s          cn38xxp2;
01501     struct cvmx_npi_ctl_status_cn31xx     cn50xx;
01502     struct cvmx_npi_ctl_status_s          cn58xx;
01503     struct cvmx_npi_ctl_status_s          cn58xxp1;
01504 };

01536 /**
01537  * cvmx_npi_dma_control
01538  *
01539  * NPI_DMA_CONTROL = DMA Control Register
01540  *
01541  * Controls operation of the DMA IN/OUT of the NPI.
01542  */
01543 union cvmx_npi_dma_control {
01544     uint64_t u64;
01545     struct cvmx_npi_dma_control_s {
01546 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
01547     uint64_t reserved_36_63               : 28;
01548     uint64_t b0_lend                      : 1;  /**< When set '1' and the NPI is in the mode to write
01549                                                          0 to L2C memory when a DMA is done, the address
01550                                                          to be written to will be treated as a Little
01551                                                          Endian address. This field is new to PASS-2. */
01552     uint64_t dwb_denb                     : 1;  /**< When set '1' the NPI will send a value in the DWB
01553                                                          field for a free page operation for the memory
01554                                                          that contained the data in N3. */
01555     uint64_t dwb_ichk                     : 9;  /**< When Instruction Chunks for DMA operations are freed
01556                                                          this value is used for the DWB field of the
01557                                                          operation. */
01558     uint64_t fpa_que                      : 3;  /**< The FPA queue that the instruction-chunk page will
01559                                                          be returned to when used. */
01560     uint64_t o_add1                       : 1;  /**< When set '1' 1 will be added to the DMA counters,
01561                                                          if '0' then the number of bytes in the dma transfer
01562                                                          will be added to the count register. */
01563     uint64_t o_ro                         : 1;  /**< Relaxed Ordering Mode for DMA. */
01564     uint64_t o_ns                         : 1;  /**< Nosnoop For DMA. */
01565     uint64_t o_es                         : 2;  /**< Endian Swap Mode for DMA. */
01566     uint64_t o_mode                       : 1;  /**< Select PCI_POINTER MODE to be used.
01567                                                          '1' use pointer values for address and register
01568                                                          values for RO, ES, and NS, '0' use register
01569                                                          values for address and pointer values for
01570                                                          RO, ES, and NS. */
01571     uint64_t hp_enb                       : 1;  /**< Enables the High Priority DMA.
01572                                                          While this bit is disabled '0' then the value
01573                                                          in the NPI_HIGHP_IBUFF_SADDR is re-loaded to the
01574                                                          starting address of the High Priority DMA engine.
01575                                                          CSIZE field will be reloaded, for the High Priority
01576                                                          DMA Engine. */
01577     uint64_t lp_enb                       : 1;  /**< Enables the Low Priority DMA.
01578                                                          While this bit is disabled '0' then the value
01579                                                          in the NPI_LOWP_IBUFF_SADDR is re-loaded to the
01580                                                          starting address of the Low Priority DMA engine.
01581                                                          PASS-2: When this bit is '0' the value in the
01582                                                          CSIZE field will be reloaded, for the Low Priority
01583                                                          DMA Engine. */
01584     uint64_t csize                        : 14; /**< The size in words of the DMA Instruction Chunk.
01585                                                          This value should only be written once. After
01586                                                          writing this value a new value will not be
01587                                                          recognized until the end of the DMA I-Chunk is
01588                                                          reached. */
01589 #else
01590     uint64_t csize                        : 14;
01591     uint64_t lp_enb                       : 1;
01592     uint64_t hp_enb                       : 1;
01593     uint64_t o_mode                       : 1;
01594     uint64_t o_es                         : 2;
01595     uint64_t o_ns                         : 1;
01596     uint64_t o_ro                         : 1;
01597     uint64_t o_add1                       : 1;
01598     uint64_t fpa_que                      : 3;
01599     uint64_t dwb_ichk                     : 9;
01600     uint64_t dwb_denb                     : 1;
01601     uint64_t b0_lend                      : 1;
01602     uint64_t reserved_36_63               : 28;
01603 #endif
01604     } s;
01605     struct cvmx_npi_dma_control_s         cn30xx;
01606     struct cvmx_npi_dma_control_s         cn31xx;
01607     struct cvmx_npi_dma_control_s         cn38xx;
01608     struct cvmx_npi_dma_control_s         cn38xxp2;
01609     struct cvmx_npi_dma_control_s         cn50xx;
01610     struct cvmx_npi_dma_control_s         cn58xx;

02607                                                          data this bit may be set. */

02609                                                          data this bit may be set. */

02621                                                          read packet data. */

02623                                                          doorbell count was set. */
02624     uint64_t i2_overf                     : 1;  /**< Port-2 had a doorbell overflow. Bit[31] of the
02625                                                          doorbell count was set. */

02628     uint64_t i0_overf                     : 1;  /**< Port-0 had a doorbell overflow. Bit[31] of the

02631                                                          read instructions. */
02632     uint64_t i2_rtout                     : 1;  /**< Port-2 had a read timeout while attempting to
02633                                                          read instructions. */
02634     uint64_t i1_rtout                     : 1;  /**< Port-1 had a read timeout while attempting to
02635                                                          read instructions. */
02636     uint64_t i0_rtout                     : 1;  /**< Port-0 had a read timeout while attempting to
02637                                                          read instructions. */
02638     uint64_t po3_2sml                     : 1;  /**< The packet being sent out on Port3 is smaller
02639                                                          than the NPI_BUFF_SIZE_OUTPUT3[ISIZE] field. */
02640     uint64_t po2_2sml                     : 1;  /**< The packet being sent out on Port2 is smaller
02641                                                          than the NPI_BUFF_SIZE_OUTPUT2[ISIZE] field. */
02642     uint64_t po1_2sml                     : 1;  /**< The packet being sent out on Port1 is smaller
02643                                                          than the NPI_BUFF_SIZE_OUTPUT1[ISIZE] field. */
02644     uint64_t po0_2sml                     : 1;  /**< The packet being sent out on Port0 is smaller
02645                                                          than the NPI_BUFF_SIZE_OUTPUT0[ISIZE] field. */
02646     uint64_t pci_rsl                      : 1;  /**< This '1' when a bit in PCI_INT_SUM2 is SET and the
02647                                                          corresponding bit in the PCI_INT_ENB2 is SET. */
02648     uint64_t rml_wto                      : 1;  /**< Set '1' when the RML does not receive a commit

03165 /**
03166  * cvmx_npi_mem_access_subid#
03167  *
03168  * NPI_MEM_ACCESS_SUBID3 = Memory Access SubId 3Register
03169  *
03170  * Carries Read/Write parameters for PP access to PCI memory that use NPI SubId3.
03171  * Writes to this register are not ordered with writes/reads to the PCI Memory space.
03172  * To ensure that a write has completed the user must read the register before
03173  * making an access(i.e. PCI memory space) that requires the value of this register to be updated.
03174  */

03181                                                          Loads from the cores to the corresponding subid
03182                                                          that are 32-bits or smaller:
03183                                                          - Will generate the PCI-X "Memory Read DWORD"
03184                                                            command in PCI-X mode. (Note that "Memory
03185                                                            Read DWORD" appears much like an IO read on
03186                                                            the PCI-X bus.)
03187                                                          - Will generate the PCI "Memory Read" command
03188                                                            in PCI-X mode, irrespective of the
03189                                                            NPI_PCI_READ_CMD[CMD_SIZE] value.
03190                                                          NOT IN PASS 1 NOR PASS 2 */
03191     uint64_t nmerge                       : 1;  /**< No Merge. (NOT IN PASS 1 NOR PASS 2) */
03192     uint64_t esr                          : 2;  /**< Endian-Swap on read. */
03193     uint64_t esw                          : 2;  /**< Endian-Swap on write. */
03194     uint64_t nsr                          : 1;  /**< No-Snoop on read. */
03195     uint64_t nsw                          : 1;  /**< No-Snoop on write. */
03196     uint64_t ror                          : 1;  /**< Relax Read on read. */
03197     uint64_t row                          : 1;  /**< Relax Order on write. */
03198     uint64_t ba                           : 28; /**< PCI Address bits [63:36]. */
03199 #else
03200     uint64_t ba                           : 28;
03201     uint64_t row                          : 1;
03202     uint64_t ror                          : 1;
03203     uint64_t nsw                          : 1;
03204     uint64_t nsr                          : 1;
03205     uint64_t esw                          : 2;
03206     uint64_t esr                          : 2;
03207     uint64_t nmerge                       : 1;
03208     uint64_t shortl                       : 1;
03209     uint64_t reserved_38_63               : 26;
03210 #endif
03211     } s;
03212     struct cvmx_npi_mem_access_subidx_s   cn30xx;

03888                                                          value is used the packet reads and is clamped at

03913 /**
03914  * cvmx_npi_pci_int_arb_cfg
03915  *
03916  * NPI_PCI_INT_ARB_CFG = Configuration For PCI Arbiter
03917  *
03918  * Controls operation of the Internal PCI Arbiter.  This register should
03919  * only be written when PRST# is asserted.  NPI_PCI_INT_ARB_CFG[EN] should
03920  * only be set when Octane is a host.
03921  */
03922 union cvmx_npi_pci_int_arb_cfg {
03923     uint64_t u64;
03924     struct cvmx_npi_pci_int_arb_cfg_s {
03925 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
03926     uint64_t reserved_13_63               : 51;
03927     uint64_t hostmode                     : 1;  /**< PCI Host Mode Pin (sampled for use by software).
03928                                                          This bit reflects the sampled PCI_HOSTMODE pin.
03929                                                          In HOST Mode, OCTEON drives the PCI_CLK_OUT and
03930                                                          PCI initialization pattern during PCI_RST_N deassertion). */
03931     uint64_t pci_ovr                      : 4;  /**< PCI Host Mode Bus Speed/Type Override
03932                                                           When in Host Mode(PCI_HOSTMODE pin =1), OCTEON acting
03933                                                           as the PCI Central Agent, samples the PCI_PCI100,
03934                                                           PCI_M66EN and PCI_PCIXCAP pins to determine the
03935                                                           'sampled' PCI Bus speed and Bus Type (PCI or PCIX).
03936                                                           (see: PCI_CNT_REG[HM_SPEED,HM_PCIX])
03937                                                           However, in some cases, SW may want to override the
03938                                                           the 'sampled' PCI Bus Type/Speed, and use some
03939                                                           SLOWER Bus frequency.
03940                                                           The PCI_OVR field encoding represents the 'override'
03941                                                           PCI Bus Type/Speed which will be used to generate the
03942                                                           PCI_CLK_OUT and determines the PCI initialization pattern
03943                                                           driven during PCI_RST_N deassertion.
03944                                                               PCI_OVR[3]: OVERRIDE (0:DISABLE/1:ENABLE)
03945                                                               PCI_OVR[2]: BUS TYPE(0:PCI/1:PCIX)
03946                                                               PCI_OVR[1:0]: BUS SPEED(0:33/1:66/2:100/3:133)
03947                                                          OVERRIDE TYPE SPEED |  Override Configuration
03948                                                             [3]   [2]  [1:0] | TYPE       SPEED
03949                                                            ------------------+-------------------------------
03950                                                              0     x      xx | No override(uses 'sampled'
03951                                                                              | Bus Speed(HM_SPEED) and Bus Type(HM_PCIX)
03952                                                              1     0      00 | PCI Mode    33MHz
03953                                                              1     0      01 | PCI Mode    66MHz
03954                                                              1     0      10 | RESERVED (DO NOT USE)
03955                                                              1     0      11 | RESERVED (DO NOT USE)
03956                                                              1     1      00 | RESERVED (DO NOT USE)
03957                                                              1     1      01 | PCIX Mode   66MHz
03958                                                              1     1      10 | PCIX Mode  100MHz
03959                                                              1     1      11 | PCIX Mode  133MHz
03960                                                           NOTES:
03961                                                           - NPI_PCI_INT_ARB_CFG[PCI_OVR] has NO EFFECT on
03962                                                             PCI_CNT_REG[HM_SPEED,HM_PCIX] (ie: the sampled PCI Bus
03963                                                             Type/Speed), but WILL EFFECT PCI_CTL_STATUS_2[AP_PCIX]
03964                                                             which reflects the actual PCI Bus Type(0:PCI/1:PCIX).
03965                                                           - Software should never 'up' configure the recommended values.
03966                                                             In other words, if the 'sampled' Bus Type=PCI(HM_PCIX=0),
03967                                                             then SW should NOT attempt to set TYPE[2]=1 for PCIX Mode.
03968                                                             Likewise, if the sampled Bus Speed=66MHz(HM_SPEED=01),
03969                                                             then SW should NOT attempt to 'speed up' the bus [ie:
03970                                                             SPEED[1:0]=10(100MHz)].
03971                                                           - If PCI_OVR<3> is set prior to PCI reset de-assertion
03972                                                             in host mode, NPI_PCI_INT_ARB_CFG[PCI_OVR]
03973                                                             indicates the Bus Type/Speed that OCTEON drove on the
03974                                                             DEVSEL/STOP/TRDY pins during reset de-assertion. (user
03975                                                             should then ignore the 'sampled' Bus Type/Speed
03976                                                             contained in the PCI_CNT_REG[HM_PCIX, HM_SPEED]) fields.
03977                                                           - If PCI_OVR<3> is clear prior to PCI reset de-assertion
03978                                                             in host mode, PCI_CNT_REG[HM_PCIX,HM_SPEED])
03979                                                             indicates the Bus Type/Speed that OCTEON drove on the
03980                                                             DEVSEL/STOP/TRDY pins during reset de-assertion. */
03981     uint64_t reserved_5_7                 : 3;
03982     uint64_t en                           : 1;  /**< Internal arbiter enable. */
03983     uint64_t park_mod                     : 1;  /**< Bus park mode. 0=park on last, 1=park on device. */
03984     uint64_t park_dev                     : 3;  /**< Bus park device. 0-3 External device, 4 = Octane. */
03985 #else
03986     uint64_t park_dev                     : 3;
03987     uint64_t park_mod                     : 1;
03988     uint64_t en                           : 1;
03989     uint64_t reserved_5_7                 : 3;
03990     uint64_t pci_ovr                      : 4;
03991     uint64_t hostmode                     : 1;
03992     uint64_t reserved_13_63               : 51;
03993 #endif
03994     } s;
03995     struct cvmx_npi_pci_int_arb_cfg_cn30xx {
03996 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
03997     uint64_t reserved_5_63                : 59;
03998     uint64_t en                           : 1;  /**< Internal arbiter enable. */
03999     uint64_t park_mod                     : 1;  /**< Bus park mode. 0=park on last, 1=park on device. */
04000     uint64_t park_dev                     : 3;  /**< Bus park device. 0-3 External device, 4 = Octane. */
04001 #else
04002     uint64_t park_dev                     : 3;
04003     uint64_t park_mod                     : 1;
04004     uint64_t en                           : 1;
04005     uint64_t reserved_5_63                : 59;
04006 #endif
04007     } cn30xx;
04008     struct cvmx_npi_pci_int_arb_cfg_cn30xx cn31xx;
04009     struct cvmx_npi_pci_int_arb_cfg_cn30xx cn38xx;
04010     struct cvmx_npi_pci_int_arb_cfg_cn30xx cn38xxp2;
04011     struct cvmx_npi_pci_int_arb_cfg_s     cn50xx;
04012     struct cvmx_npi_pci_int_arb_cfg_s     cn58xx;
04013     struct cvmx_npi_pci_int_arb_cfg_s     cn58xxp1;
04014 };
04015 typedef union cvmx_npi_pci_int_arb_cfg cvmx_npi_pci_int_arb_cfg_t;

04017 /**
04018  * cvmx_npi_pci_read_cmd
04019  *
04020  * NPI_PCI_READ_CMD = NPI PCI Read Command Register
04021  *
04022  * Controls the type of read command sent.
04023  * Writes to this register are not ordered with writes/reads to the PCI Memory space.
04024  * To ensure that a write has completed the user must read the register before
04025  * making an access(i.e. PCI memory space) that requires the value of this register to be updated.
04026  * Also any previously issued reads/writes to PCI memory space, still stored in the outbound
04027  * FIFO will use the value of this register after it has been updated.
04028  */

04032 #ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN_BITFIELD
04033     uint64_t reserved_11_63               : 53;
04034     uint64_t cmd_size                     : 11; /**< Number bytes to be read is equal to or exceeds this
04035                                                          size will cause the PCI in PCI mode to use a
04036                                                          Memory-Read-Multiple. This register has a value
04037                                                          from 8 to 2048. A value of 0-7 will be treated as
04038                                                          a value of 2048. */
04039 #else
04040     uint64_t cmd_size                     : 11;
04041     uint64_t reserved_11_63               : 53;
04042 #endif
04043     } s;
04044     struct cvmx_npi_pci_read_cmd_s        cn30xx;
04045     struct cvmx_npi_pci_read_cmd_s        cn31xx;
04046     struct cvmx_npi_pci_read_cmd_s        cn38xx;

04048     struct cvmx_npi_pci_read_cmd_s        cn50xx;
04049     struct cvmx_npi_pci_read_cmd_s        cn58xx;
04050     struct cvmx_npi_pci_read_cmd_s        cn58xxp1;

04231     uint64_t rsv_f                        : 5;  /**< Reserved */

04233     uint64_t rsv_e                        : 1;  /**< Reserved */
04234     uint64_t rskp_len                     : 7;  /**< Skip Length. Used when packet is raw and PBP==0. */
04235     uint64_t rsv_d                        : 6;  /**< Reserved */

04237                                                          as part of the packet data, regardless of the

04239                                                          USE_IHDR must be set whenever PBP is set. */
04240     uint64_t rsv_c                        : 5;  /**< Reserved */

04242                                                          is not raw and PBP is not set. */
04243     uint64_t rsv_b                        : 1;  /**< Reserved
04244                                                          instruction header sent to IPD. */
04245     uint64_t skp_len                      : 7;  /**< Skip Length. Used when USE_IHDR is set and packet
04246                                                          is not raw and PBP is not set. */
04247     uint64_t rsv_a                        : 6;  /**< Reserved */
04248 #else
04249     uint64_t rsv_a                        : 6;
04250     uint64_t skp_len                      : 7;
04251     uint64_t rsv_b                        : 1;
04252     uint64_t par_mode                     : 2;
04253     uint64_t rsv_c                        : 5;
04254     uint64_t use_ihdr                     : 1;
04255     uint64_t rsv_d                        : 6;
04256     uint64_t rskp_len                     : 7;
04257     uint64_t rsv_e                        : 1;
04258     uint64_t rparmode                     : 2;
04259     uint64_t rsv_f                        : 5;
04260     uint64_t pbp                          : 1;

04262 #endif
